# NeuraForge AI — Kiro CLI Rules

Read AGENTS.md for full instructions on code generation, review, debugging, and architecture principles.

## Hub & Blade Architecture

NeuraForge uses a Unified Hub (MCP server) for shared services. The Hub is a TOOLBOX, not an orchestrator.

**Hub tools available:**
- `state_*` — pipeline state management (init, advance, loop, list)
- `govern_*` — permission checks, boundary enforcement, handoff validation
- `analytics_*` — event logging, metrics
- `critical_*` — critical items accumulation (add, resolve, defer, override)
- `lock_*` — cross-pipeline mutual exclusion

**Orchestration:** The `feature-pipeline` agent is the orchestrator. It follows a deterministic checklist and uses Hub tools for state management and enforcement.

## Key Rules
- Search codebase before creating new code
- Plan before acting — present approach, wait for approval
- Reuse → Extend → Refactor → Create (never duplicate)
- Controllers <150 lines, services <300, components <150
- Data fetching at the leaf level
- Loading / Error / Empty states on every screen
- All handoffs use protocol v3 (see rules/core/HANDOFF_PROTOCOL.md)

